text:
to all the men out there, 
i want to love you.

i want to hold you, 
i want to hear you, 
i want to feel you, 
i want to make space for you, 
i want to hug you, 
i want to nurture you, 
i want to appreciate you.

i want you to break down before me and cry, 
i want you to tell me about your pain, 
i want you to hold my hand,
i want you to tell me what you don‚Äôt know, 
i want you to share your heart with me, 
i want you to allow my love to enter.

and may we embrace, forgive, and realize, 
all abuse was a plea for love, 
all hoarding a symbol of emptiness, 
all knowing a sign of unworthiness.

so what may have seemed unfair, 
is now shown to be the divine‚Äôs way of giving to those who were less able to give to themselves.

and my perceived victim identity, 
merely a trick to awaken to my own power, 
to help me see beyond manipulation, 
to the truth that i‚Äôm in control, 
enabling me to be here now to hold space,
so others can do the same.

what women endured out of love for men and what men inflicted on women out of love and awakening for them, 
can now be brought to the light, 
seen for what it truly is, 
love, in all it‚Äôs different forms.

may we all heal to open our eyes to the beauty and perfection before us. 
may we all appreciate each other‚Äôs differences in both masculine and feminine form. 
may we all reframe evil into pain, realizing in that way we‚Äôre all the same. 
may we all know our value and worth beyond the physical, into the eternal. 
may we all embrace each other and honor the sacrifice and pain we have endured to heal our planet and bring us into an age of peace and prosperity for all beings. 
may we all awaken to who we really are, fall in love with who we truly are, and from that place, greet our fellow human with the vibration of our heart.

for a long time i‚Äôve wanted to do a piece that emboldened the female fight. knowing you‚Äôre allowed to be confident in your body and that doesn‚Äôt mean it‚Äôs sexual or an invitation. but art is all interpretation. my art isn‚Äôt free from imperfections but neither are we. i painted this for a reason but maybe you view it differently. i‚Äôd love to hear how you see it. 
i couldn‚Äôt have done this alone. i want to thank @azraelrenee for being an amazing model. she is an awesome inspiration for girls (and guys) everywhere. keep being rad. thanks to @themudcrusher for pushing me to finish this piece. strong females like you are what this is about. for my friends @nadinesinstagram @laurenmcrae311 and @m_hudgins for being awesome sounding boards and inspiration. and to all the strong females in my life, keep fighting, this is for you. 
in the future i will sell this piece and profit will go towards a charity that helps women. if you‚Äôre interested, send me a dm, or stay tuned!

text:
- she [rebekah mercer] loved me. she was like, oh we need more of your type on our side!

your type? - the gays. she loved the gays. so did steve [bannon]. he saw us as early adopters. he figured, if you can get the gays on board, everyone else will follow. it‚Äôs why he was so into the whole milo [yiannopoulos] thing.

robert mercer was a pioneer in ai and machine translation. he helped invent algorithmic trading ‚Äì which replaced hedge fund managers with computer programs ‚Äì and he listened to wylie‚Äôs pitch. it was for a new kind of political message-targeting based on an influential and groundbreaking 2014 paper researched at cambridge‚Äôs psychometrics centre, called: - computer-based personality judgments are more accurate than those made by humans. - in politics, the money man is usually the dumbest person in the room. whereas it‚Äôs the opposite way around with mercer, says wylie. - he said very little, but he really listened. he wanted to understand the science. and he wanted proof that it worked.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

your type? - the gays. she loved the gays. so did steve [bannon]. he saw us as early adopters. he figured, if you can get the gays on board, everyone else will follow. it‚Äôs why he was so into the whole milo [yiannopoulos] thing.

robert mercer was a pioneer in ai and machine translation. he helped invent algorithmic trading ‚Äì which replaced hedge fund managers with computer programs ‚Äì and he listened to wylie‚Äôs pitch. it was for a new kind of political message-targeting based on an influential and groundbreaking 2014 paper researched at cambridge‚Äôs psychometrics centre, called: - computer-based personality judgments are more accurate than those made by humans. - in politics, the money man is usually the dumbest person in the room. whereas it‚Äôs the opposite way around with mercer, says wylie. - he said very little, but he really listened. he wanted to understand the science. and he wanted proof that it worked.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

como sou demasiado competitivo em tudo o que fa√ßo, esfor√ßo-me muito para ser o melhor na ansiedade. foi por isso que aos 18 anos fiz upgrade da ansiedade para o s√≠ndrome de p√¢nico. o c√©rebro humano foi concebido para ter 3 ataques de p√¢nico durante a vida toda. o caso mais comum √© se a casa estiver a arder. j√° eu, basta-me queimar as torradas.

estudos dizem que 1 em cada 5 pessoas ja sofreu de uma doen√ßa mental. n√£o sei, estudos tamb√©m dizem que 4 em cada 5 estudos s√£o aldrabice. sei que n√£o estou sozinho. perdi conta √†s mensagens a agradecer os √∫ltimos 10 minutos do meu espet√°culo. sinto-me ego√≠sta porque fi-lo a pensar s√≥ em mim, n√£o para dar voz a algu√©m.

durante 12 anos guardei isto tudo para mim. em puto quando ia ao pc do meu pai apagava o hist√≥rico n√£o por ver pornografia mas porque ia l√° pesquisar sobre agorafobia.

em portugal ouvimos sempre os mesmos debates sobre se foi fora-de-jogo do jonas, mas pouco se fala de sa√∫de mental. problemas mentais s√£o sempre ‚Äúcoisas l√° da cabe√ßa deles‚Äù, mas quando algu√©m parte um joelho nunca s√£o coisas l√° da r√≥tula dele.

numa √©poca com movimentos t√£o importantes como o #metoo ou #blacklivesmatter, gostava de ver um pela sa√∫de mental. mas um obsessivo-compulsivo como eu demoraria 7 anos s√≥ para escolher a hashtag.

hesitei demasiado tempo se deveria partilhar isto publicamente. porque sou homem, branco e heterossexual. nunca tive de lutar pelo meu espa√ßo. sei que sou um privilegiado. n√£o imagino aquilo por que passa um homossexual para ‚Äúsair do arm√°rio‚Äù, se a mim que (s√≥) tenho ansiedade j√° me custa sair de casa.

estou cansado de fazer humor com problemas que n√£o tenho. n√£o me interessa se primeiro vem o leite ou os cereais, primeiro vem sempre a ansiedade.

no meu √∫ltimo post de 2018, chamo √† aten√ß√£o para a sa√∫de mental. da minha aprendizagem, o primeiro passo √© pedir ajuda. ningu√©m aprende a andar de bicicleta sozinho.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn‚Äôs don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica‚Äôs parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan‚Äôs app may not have been completely deleted. kogan‚Äôs app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
cambridge analytica, which was shut down earlier this year following an investigation by the observer, was the political marketing firm headed by trump‚Äôs former key adviser, steve bannon, and owned by hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. it also used user information obtained without authorisation in early 2014 ‚Äì including cultural preferences such as fashion and music ‚Äì to create a system that could single out voters in order to expose them to specific political advertising.

prior to the company‚Äôs role on trump‚Äôs election campaign, wylie had been its director of research. recalling his first meeting with bannon, he explained how fashion was one of the many things they examined, along with ‚Äújudith butler, foucault and nature of our fractured self‚Äù. he said the pair discussed the difference between crocs and chanel‚Äôs little black dress as analogous for the fashion spectrum ‚Äì which would become a blueprint for how the firm used fashion preferences later on.

wylie went onto to criticise the fashion industry for creating a ‚Äúpre-existing cultural foundation which allowed the alt-right to grow over that time period‚Äù. he conceded that while cambridge analytica ‚Äúexploited the cultural narratives that the fashion and culture industry put out‚Äù, the fashion industry was responsible for creating those cultural narratives in the first place. he added: ‚Äúwe need new narratives in culture, and to do a better job of showing more diversity‚Äù in order to direct politics along a different route.

according to the data obtained (the majority of which came from us users), certain fans of american denim brands such as wrangler, hollister and lee jeans could be more closely linked to low levels of openness and mistrust ‚Äì and therefore more likely to engage with pro-trump messaging.

morwenna ferrier
the guardian

prior to the company‚Äôs role on trump‚Äôs election campaign, wylie had been its director of research. recalling his first meeting with bannon, he explained how fashion was one of the many things they examined, along with ‚Äújudith butler, foucault and nature of our fractured self‚Äù. he said the pair discussed the difference between crocs and chanel‚Äôs little black dress as analogous for the fashion spectrum ‚Äì which would become a blueprint for how the firm used fashion preferences later on.

wylie went onto to criticise the fashion industry for creating a ‚Äúpre-existing cultural foundation which allowed the alt-right to grow over that time period‚Äù. he conceded that while cambridge analytica ‚Äúexploited the cultural narratives that the fashion and culture industry put out‚Äù, the fashion industry was responsible for creating those cultural narratives in the first place. he added: ‚Äúwe need new narratives in culture, and to do a better job of showing more diversity‚Äù in order to direct politics along a different route.

according to the data obtained (the majority of which came from us users), ceain fans of american denim brands such as wrangler, hollister and lee jeans could be more closely linked to low levels of openness and mistrust ‚Äì and therefore more likely to engage with pro-trump messaging.

text:
thank you to the amazing photographer @ken.rochon for this.

2018 has been a roller coaster ride, smiling has kept me focused on the truth and reality of life.

we are travelling through times of great conflict, change and challenge.  2019 welcomes us all to lift our game, collaborate for the good of all and seek wisdom in unlikely places... wisdom found in the chatter of youth of today and the silver elders wise across decades, all equally received, with women and men valuing differences as a positive energy force, in the boardroom and bedroom, people not changing others against their will.

opening our minds, hearts and willingness to serve each have other in families, communities, countries and continents. üåçüåéüåè let's move beyond any confusion and find clarity of meaning, live life with loving intentions.

#magicalconversations #soulmatelove #genderdynamics #itstimetotalk #worldharmony #metoo

.
- puis @voxvulva va citer ce qui au final est un oui ou un non :
oui = oui .... et tout ce qui n'est pas oui = non.
... donc non = non
... peut √™tre = non
... je ne sais pas = non .
... je ne suis pas s√ªr = non
... pas de parole = non
et finalement... oui = oui.
.
- puis @voxvulva affirme que le sexe passe par une communication claire pour "√™tre certain(e) du consentement de son/sa partenaire" qui va permettre de s'assurer qu'on n'est pas en train de violer son/sa partenaire".
.
- mais pr√©cise que le consentement peut √©voluer et √™tre retir√© √† tout moment de l'acte sexuel... on peut changer d'avis... et il faut "respecter cela", sinon c'est un viol.
.
- @voxvulva finit par une pr√©cision importante : souvent la vision du consentement n'inclus pas la notion de d√©sir et le parall√®le est fait sur l'id√©e tenace que le d√©sir d'une femme depuis sa plus tendre enfance est bafou√©, ignor√©,  ni√© ...
.

my #topnine hits were all of me learning to take up space and own that space with pride and joy, whether it was my fitness transformations, or work goals met! i worked in hawaii on @hawaiifive0cbs in my first top of show guest, i did countless hours of spin, hiit, yoga, and weight training (targeting your glutes with heavy weights absolutely works wonders), i shot with @mollypanphotography which you all loved. üíì
but there were also life-changing events not pictured here. i also lost two kitty babies, one to old age and cancer, one to the deadly wet form of fip shortly after adopting her, both of which were devastating to me. my #metoo experience was doubted and questioned by now former friends, my integrity was challenged about my adoption of sasha (the kitten with fip) by a now estranged friend whom i had devoted a lot of care and understanding to in her difficult times this year, and i had a rough few months of learning to love myself enough to leave bad situations in order to make space for new better ones. üôèüèΩ
if there‚Äôs one major lesson i learned this year, it‚Äôs that we are each on our own journey through life and sometimes paths diverge and rejoin, and other times they diverge with no intersection in sight, but we all have work to do on ourselves, flaws to work on, grudges to release, habits to change, and sometimes the only person that can help you is the one you can‚Äôt run away from: yourself. üôåüèΩ
it‚Äôs okay if that one friend can‚Äôt be there for you. maybe they are battling their own demons and don‚Äôt have the strength to take on anything else. you will make new friends. you have other friends you can lean on, too. and you will always have yourself, and your inner reserve of strength that is deeper than you can know. üôáüèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è
with that in mind, may those of us who tend to live for others remember in 2019, to also live for ourselves and put ourselves first now and again, and may those who often elevate their own needs above others remember theirs is not always the most pressing or important. we all have intrinsic value and can be stronger when we work together but there may be tasks only we can complete alone. üë¨üë≠üë´
ü•Ç to #2019

text:
its a special kind of sunday morning when a message pings in.

i love it that still the haters keep on coming with their 'opinions about what i am and what i have 'done ', each one choosing a bit of my story to challenge.

accusations of will tampering, theft, lies and daring to go to the cinema after my nan died!
he didn't go so far to say i ate babies and murdered cats for pleasure, but, hey give it time, .......... it's strange how they believe one thing and then challenge other ridiculous details which they put a whole new spin on to make it suit their opinions!

i feel sorry for them all that have have not the ability, intelligence nor empathy to accept that our lives were different, that there were things they never knew and situations which they could never have grasped because they didn't walk my shoes.

having empathy and the ability to acknowledge other's opinions is a gift and one which is not rife in my birth gene pool, but one which is thankfully present in abundance in the friends and network who i chose to be part of.

i don't feel the need to respond to their poison, but have taken steps today to stop their lies, malicious postings and blatant bullying.

it's been a steep learning curve for me in 2018, learning to hear their noise and change it into beautiful music as i spread my message to other survivors of adversity and abuse that when you know your truth and feel at peace with it you will be strong and passionate in your path to speak out and help other's. 
my voice may shake, along with my knees yet my truth remains.

#survivors #metoo #timesup #warriors #memoir #mytruth #raiseourvoices #perception #endviolence 
@dailyhappytimes @rsvpwm @womenshealthuk @forwomenwhoroar @unwomen @you_are_not_crazy @womenshealthmag @oprah @forgivenessproj @womenwithgifts @lorraine

text:
you forgot to have fun. huh?

you been hustling and failing and winning all 2018.

looking at the past, measuring the goals, murdering yourself to hit a weight loss objective and you have been killing yourself.

in the process of doing all this stuff...somehow, some way, you forgot to have fun...huh?

i said this to myself. if one of your goals for 2019 is not having a fuggin blast then what the hell are you doing it for.

soooooo i walked my big ass in the lego store (with a beautiful little boy i was taking care of). as they looked up at me like i was godzilla in japan, i realized a couple things. 
1. i get a kick out of being godzilla
2. have some fuggin fun.

so i stopped showing him stuff...and started to just play myself. 
i grabbed wigs and arms and legs and feet and income tax returns (joking) but in grabbed all that stuff and really just had a moment for myself. it was dope!!! dont forget to have fun along the way. your spirit requests it.

have fuggin fun, that's how to be a firestarter!!! .
.
.
.
.

two child refugees held in us custody died in the space of a month. the first was a girl who travelled for over a week with her father to escape poverty. when she arrived at the border she was detained and not given any water, and later died of dehydration and exhaustion. the second was a boy who also travelled from guatemala. he died of pre existing health issues. however, he wasn‚Äôt provided with proper care or medical attention. these children were innocent, they did nothing wrong. yet there are still people who would rather give money to build a wall and prevent an imaginary threat than help prevent innocent children dying. immigrants and refugees aren‚Äôt a threat, the us is.

text:
what is it about addicts in their addiction that make them so convincing, their arguments that what they‚Äôre doing is ok, even when their loved ones try to tell them their behavior is destructive? 
i once had a friend who fresh out of rehab gave me his secret on how he does this: ‚Äúi recruit other friends and people who agree with what i‚Äôm doing.‚Äù üî•boom. we can all find people, even therapists who will help us justify crappy behavior, especially when we‚Äôre in charge of the narrative, we‚Äôre the victim. 
i‚Äôm going to give you the secret on how to deal with people like this, even when you love them. and here is where families are strengthened or destroyed, because if the family buys into the addict‚Äôs narrative, the entire family will. go. down. ‚ù§Ô∏èwalk away in love. 
get out of the water- it‚Äôs toxic, & you may have bought into this way for so long that you may not even realize how sick the whole family is, including you. if you stay in the water with the addict, you‚Äôre going to help kill him & destroy yourself. see the toxicity. realize it may seem normal because it‚Äôs all you know. you must fight to find a new ocean to swim in. 
families die out when the addiction rules.
families thrive when they say they‚Äôve had enough of the bullshit & choose to walk away.  you can love an addict to death by showing ‚Äúunconditional love.‚Äù addicts love to hear that. translation: ‚Äú i can do what i want & they should still accept me.‚Äù you see, they‚Äôre looking for more recruits to justify. pull away from them & you‚Äôll hear ‚Äúyou only love me conditionally! that‚Äôs not fair!‚Äù show them love & then let them go. they‚Äôre ‚Äúgoing‚Äù anyway. 
what happened to my friend? he went to rehab a second time & there he found other addicts to help justify his destructive ways. last i saw him he was going to ride the horse of ‚Äúi‚Äôm completely healthy,‚Äù until he died. naked as a jaybird to everyone else, the emperor with no clothes on, & yes, luckily his family had walked away in love. to his detriment though he had other people waiting for him to help justify his choices, & some of them were just as sick. birds of a feather in toxic waters. see facebook for more content

text:
for the woman who has experienced sexual trauma, you are not alone and there is hope for healing. maybe it's time to take the next step in your journey to heal. join us for the next seven week journey to heal women's group taking place at port city community church starting tuesday, january 15th from 6:30-8:30pm. groups are available at both the wilmington and leland campuses. registration is free, but required. learn more about jth groups and register for either location at journeytohealministries.org/programs/groups.
.

text: i haven‚Äôt publicly made this known and why now... i am not exactly sure. over the past few years, i have finally come to terms with the fact that i have #fybromaliga. it isn‚Äôt the easiest diagnosis to get let alone come to terms with. tonight i had a fun mini #datenight planned for aj and i. just some much needed alone time after some really busy days and weeks recently. while we pulled up to dinner i started not feeling well. once we got into the restaurant, i drank some water and had some bread hoping that i would feel a little better. after ordering, i looked at aj and said, ‚Äúi am so sorry baby, but i really think i need to go home.‚Äù it comes out of no where. you feel fine and then honestly within seconds you want to crawl under the covers, go to bed and wait for the next day to come. sadly, my nicely planned date night changed that quickly. within minutes i went from excited to have a dinner with my husband at one of our favorite little waukesha gems to wanting to cry from the pain i was in. thankfully i have an amazing and understanding partner! when i say ‚Äúgotta go!,‚Äù no questions asked, he gets the bill and takes me home. there is lots of mixed feelings about fybromaliga and i am not here to debate the opinions but i can tell you the facts. for people that struggle with #chronicpain, it is real and it does affect you. for the longest time i didn‚Äôt want to admit it. i also was scared. ‚Äúwhat if this controls my life?‚Äù what if i be come one of ‚Äúthose people?‚Äù and, honestly sometimes it can control my life and i probably am ‚Äúone of those people.‚Äù what i have learned most is that it doesn‚Äôt have to control me and i don‚Äôt have to let it affect me. almost 100% of the time i am in pain and 90% of the time i can fight through it to the point you wouldn‚Äôt even know i was hurting. for the other 10%, like tonight, my body says, ‚Äúyou are done!‚Äù and i have no say in it. .... more in comments. see below ‚¨áÔ∏è‚¨áÔ∏è‚¨áÔ∏è #geteducated #nojudgement #bestlife #fybromyalgiaawareness #fybrofighter #fybro
name: Dani & AJ

text:
thank you, all, for showing up, reading, sharing, and supporting my debut u.s. novel, ‚Äúlouisiana catch.‚Äù i am humbled: published by a progressive but small press...‚Äúlouisiana catch‚Äù won me the voices of the year award @blogher @sheknows (past recipients have been chelsea clinton and founder of the #metoo movement). the book was nominated for the pushcart prize and is listed as the top 50 fiction books of 2018 by @cyruswebbpresents‚Äîhe joins oprah winfrey network‚Äôs digital content starting march '19üôèüèºüôèüèºüôèüèº üåüüåüüåü 6-7 years in the making, #louisianacatch was an offbeat book that didn‚Äôt cater to the stereotype many wanted to believe about south asians and women, in general. but i persisted. my publisher, victor volkman, gave the novel a home and worked as hard as i did‚ù§Ô∏èüôèüèº we have results to show that our team effort bore fruits. üåüüåüüåüüåüüåü
üåü
üåü
üåü
üåüfor anyone with a dream: don‚Äôt let others opinion of you or your goals impact what you do with your life‚ù§Ô∏è no two people are alike...neither are their dreams nor their chosen paths. listen to all but do what works best for you. stay authentic and honest and focused. don‚Äôt criticize others just because you don‚Äôt understand their path. at the same time, you don‚Äôt have to concern yourself with understanding everyone‚Äôs decisionsü§∑üèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è if you believe in yourself and are willing to work harder than everybody else and not be distracted by self-created competition and insecurities, your work will find its audience...it will find the right homeüåü the quality of your writing and ability to work hard can trump the size of the press. here is wishing you a fearless, fulfilling, successful, and creative 2019‚ù§Ô∏è #bookstagram #lifeofawriter #writingadvice
name: Sweta Srivastava Vikram
